Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Eswatini as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Eswatini to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in Eswatini
For information on entering Eswatini, see Entry Requirements
From 6 May the partial lockdown was extended until further notice with minor easing around the opening of some businesses.The army and police will continue to be deployed to ensure compliance with the lockdown measures introduced:
movements outside of the home perimeter will be restricted, with exception of acquiring essential services such as healthcare, food and banking services
non-essential travel between towns will be prohibited
public transport will only operate for essential movements
food outlets and banks will be restricted to 20 people
all bars and off licenses will be closed
public gatherings of more than 20 people will be prohibited
